вҠў evaluate
  given askвҶ’question вүЎ "Imagine you and a colleague... What do you think happens to the commit history..."
  given askвҶ’target-understanding вүЎ "Whether the student has an intuition about commit graph topology вҖ” specifically, that combining two lines of work must reconcile divergent histories."
  given simulate-studentвҶ’answer вүЎ "I think the commits would just get interleaved by time?... I had to do a 'git pull' first... I think it just downloads their stuff and then my commits go on top?"
  given simulate-studentвҶ’confidence вүЎ "unsure"
  yield correct, misconceptions[], understanding-level

  вҲҙ Evaluate В«simulate-studentвҶ’answerВ» against В«askвҶ’target-understandingВ».
    Is the answer correct? If not, identify SPECIFIC misconceptions вҖ”
    not "doesn't understand rebase" but "thinks rebase creates a new branch"
    or "confuses rebase with cherry-pick." Rate understanding:
    "none" (no grasp), "partial" (some correct intuition, wrong details),
    "solid" (demonstrates understanding).

-- LLM evaluation:
-- The student shows partial intuition вҖ” they noticed that push failed and
-- pull was needed, which suggests they've encountered divergence. But they
-- have two specific misconceptions.

  yield correct вүЎ false
  yield misconceptions вүЎ [
    "Believes commit history is a single shared timeline ordered by wall-clock time вҖ” does not understand that each developer has an independent local history that diverges.",
    "Thinks 'git pull' simply downloads and stacks commits linearly вҖ” unaware that pull performs a merge (or rebase) to reconcile two divergent histories."
  ]
  yield understanding-level вүЎ "partial"

-- oracle checks:
--   вҠЁ correct вҲҲ {true, false} вҶ’ вң“ (false)
--   вҠЁ each misconception is specific and falsifiable вҶ’ вң“
--     (#1: falsifiable вҖ” show two users' commit graphs diverging)
--     (#2: falsifiable вҖ” demonstrate that pull creates a merge commit)
--   вҠЁ understanding-level вҲҲ {"none", "partial", "solid"} вҶ’ вң“ ("partial")
--   вҠЁ if correct then misconceptions is empty вҶ’ вң“ (correct=false, so vacuously satisfied)
--   вҠЁ if understanding-level = "solid" then correct = true вҶ’ вң“ (vacuous, level="partial")

