-- The rewritten вҲҙ targets the timeline misconception directly.

  yield question вүЎ "Scenario: You and your colleague both clone the same repo at 9:00 AM on Monday. You make three commits during the day (fixing a bug in login.py). Your colleague makes two commits (adding a new feature in dashboard.py). Neither of you pushes until 5:00 PM. Here's my question: at 4:59 PM, before either of you pushes вҖ” what does 'git log' show on YOUR machine? And what does 'git log' show on your COLLEAGUE'S machine? Are they the same log or different logs?"
  yield target-understanding вүЎ "That each git clone maintains its own independent commit history. Before push/pull, the two developers have genuinely different commit logs вҖ” not a shared timeline missing some entries, but two separate chains of commits that diverged from the same starting point."

