    "Counter-example: Alice and Bob both clone repo X at 9:00 AM. Alice's log shows: XвҶ’A1вҶ’A2. Bob's log shows: XвҶ’B1вҶ’B2. There is NO single timeline вҖ” there are two independent chains...",
    "git pull is NOT 'download and stack.' It's fetch + merge. Merge creates a NEW commit M whose parents are BOTH A2 and B2. The graph is a diamond shape. Alternatively, rebase REWRITES A1вҶ’A2 as A1'вҶ’A2' after B2...",
    "Git does NOT use timestamps to combine work. It uses parent pointers. Merge: find common ancestor, three-way diff, create merge commit with two parents. Rebase: replay your commits one-by-one on top, creating new commits. Neither cares about timestamps."
